The frequency of breast feeding and its duration is determined to a large extent during the first few days in a baby's life. If breast feeding is considered the only optimal and adequate way of feeding a newborn, everything should be done to create optimal conditions for this. Various aspects are discussed: how the surroundings could be improved in favor of breast feeding as well as where traditional aspects, which date partly from the time when artificial nutrition was predominant, still prevail. Solutions regarding these and other questions are suggested from the current point of view.  
